On the influence of the thermal boundary condition (e.g. on the magnetic field strength):
\begin{itemize}
 \item Larger scales and stronger magnetic field : Sakuraba and Roberts (2009)
 \item Hori 2010
 \item On the onset of convection and the scales: Sparrow et al., 1964
 \item Larger scales, for cartesian box:  Chapman and Proctor (1980)
\end{itemize}

On the influence on magnetic field on the flowfield temp
\begin{itemize}
 \item Flow changes due to dynamo action compared to thermal convection: (Olson and Glatzmaier, 1996)
 \item Convective scales become larger when magnetic field gains importance (Wicht, Stellmach 2010)
 \item increase of $l_u$ by 20 \% if magnetic field active: Takahashi et al. (2008a) 
\end{itemize}

Explain reason, why anti cyclones clearly dominate the flow field:
\begin{itemize}
 \item They need to store the large amounts of magnetic energy: Sakuraba, Kono 2000
\end{itemize}

